Unit risk = (2×10^-6) / (5 μg/L)

To simplify the calculation, we can convert the pollution level to the same unit as the excess cancer risk. 1 μg/L is equal to 10^-6 (μg/L)^-1.

Unit risk = (2×10^-6) / (5 μg/L)
Unit risk = (2×10^-6) / (5 × 10^-6 (μg/L)^-1)
Unit risk = 2/5 (μg/L)^-1

Therefore, the unit risk of this air pollutant is 2/5 (μg/L)^-1, which is equivalent to 4×10^-1 / 10^1 (μg/L)^-1, or 4×10^-2 (μg/L)^-1.
